.TH oremind 1 "@PROJECT_YEAR@" "@PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
oremind \- desktop self-observation reminder
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B oremind
.RI [ OPTION ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B oremind
runs a small Linux desktop observer in the background.  It starts without a
main window, immediately shows an observation prompt, and then repeats at the
configured interval.
.PP
Only one instance is intended to run per user session.  When a second instance
starts, it wakes the existing instance, prints a warning to standard error, and
exits.
.PP
Each prompt asks for a short activity note and optional energy, mood, and
grounding scores.  The prompt can be submitted with Enter, cancelled with
Escape, or snoozed for 30 seconds with Control-S.  Activity text is trimmed;
empty activity submissions are recorded as empty notes.
.PP
By default records are stored in
.IR ~/.observer/observer.sqlite3 .
The storage path can also point at a directory, in which case daily text log
files are written instead.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase logging verbosity.  This option may be repeated.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Decrease logging verbosity.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit successfully.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-locale " " \fILOCALE\fR
Set the UI locale before translations are initialized.  Examples include
.BR en ,
.BR zh_CN ,
.BR zh_TW ,
.BR ja ,
.BR ko ,
.BR fr ,
and
.BR de .
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-theme " " \fITHEME\fR
Set the prompt theme.  Supported values are
.B light
and
.BR dark .
The default is
.BR dark .
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-opacity " " \fINUM\fR
Set the final dialog opacity as a percentage from
.B 0
to
.BR 100 .
The default is
.BR 75 .
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-cancel " " \fINUM\fR
Exit after
.I NUM
consecutive prompt cancels.  The default is
.BR 3 .
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interval " " \fINUM\fR
Set the normal prompt interval in minutes.  Fractional values are accepted.
An interval of
.B 0
shows the startup prompt and exits after submit or cancel.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-weekstart " " \fIMmSs\fR
Set the calendar week start.  Use
.B M
or
.B m
for Monday, and
.B S
or
.B s
for Sunday.  The default is Monday.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-sqlite-db " " \fIPATH\fR
Set the storage target.  If
.I PATH
is a file path, it is used as the SQLite database.  If
.I PATH
is an existing directory, or ends with a slash, records are appended to daily
log files named
.IR yyyy-mm-dd.log .
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and license information and exit successfully.
.SH KEYBOARD
.TP
.B Enter
Submit the current prompt.  If the activity field is empty after trimming, an
empty note is saved.
.TP
.B Escape
Cancel the current prompt without saving.  By default, three consecutive
Escape cancels exit the application; change this with
.BR \-\-cancel .
.TP
.B Control-S
Snooze the prompt for 30 seconds.
.TP
.B Control-Q
Quit the application from the prompt.
.TP
.B F1
Open the statistics window from the prompt.
.TP
.B Control-H
Also opens the statistics window from the prompt.
.TP
.B Mod4-Alt-G
Show the prompt immediately while the application is waiting.  Mod4 is usually
the Windows or Super key.  This shortcut is registered through X11 on Linux.
.TP
.B Mod4-Alt-H
Open statistics/history immediately while the application is waiting.
.TP
.B Quit
Click the small Quit label in the prompt footer to exit the application.
.TP
.BR F2 ", " F3 ", " F4
Decrease energy, mood, or grounding score by half a step.
.TP
.BR F5 ", " F6 ", " F7
Increase energy, mood, or grounding score by half a step.
.SH TRAY ICON
.PP
The tray icon stays visible while
.B oremind
runs.  Left-click the icon to show the prompt immediately.  Right-click opens a
menu with
.BR Wake ,
.BR "Statistics / History" ,
and
.BR Quit .
The
.B Wake
action is equivalent to Mod4-Alt-G, and
.B Statistics / History
is equivalent to Mod4-Alt-H.
.SH STATISTICS
.TP
.B F1
Show calendar view.
.TP
.BR F5 ", " F6 ", " F7 ", " F8
Show day, week, month, or year statistics.
.TP
.B Escape
Close the statistics window.
.TP
.BR PageUp ", " PageDown
Move to the previous or next period in day, week, month, or year views.
.PP
In calendar view, select a date and click
.BR Day ,
.BR Week ,
or
.B Month
to enter the corresponding statistics view.
.SH STORAGE
.SS SQLite
The SQLite table is created automatically:
.PP
.nf
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS observations (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    prompted_at TEXT NOT NULL,
    submitted_at TEXT NOT NULL,
    energy REAL,
    mood REAL,
    grounding REAL,
    activity TEXT NOT NULL,
    quote TEXT
);
.fi
.PP
Default scores are treated as unrecorded values and are stored as
.BR NULL .
.SS Directory logs
Directory logging writes one file per day.  A record looks like:
.PP
.nf
hh:mm:ss e2.5 m3.5 g4.0 duration 1:23 submitted hh:mm:ss
    activity text
.fi
.PP
The leading time is the prompt time; the submitted time appears after the
duration field.
Score fields that remain at the default value are omitted.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid command-line options or runtime errors during startup.
.SH AUTHOR
